                            <comment id="16028685" author="joshrosen" created="Tue, 30 May 2017 00:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this was caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-20690&quot; title=&quot;Subqueries in FROM should have alias names&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-20690&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-20690&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which changed the parser to reject unaliased subqueries in the FROM clause. However, the error message that we now give isn&apos;t very helpful. I think that we should modify the parser to throw a more clear error for such queries so that it&apos;s more clear to end users that this is a behavior change rather than a bug. /cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=viirya&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;viirya&quot;&gt;viirya&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hvanhovell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hvanhovell&quot;&gt;hvanhovell&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smilegator&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smilegator&quot;&gt;smilegator&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
